According to a report by Intel Market Research, the global sleepwear and loungewear market was valued at USD 51.89 billion in 2024 and is projected to grow from USD 54.52 billion in 2025 to USD 75.72 billion by 2034, registering a CAGR of 5.7% during the forecast period. The market is expanding steadily as consumers increasingly seek apparel that combines comfort, functionality, and style. The continued adoption of hybrid work models, growing wellness awareness, and innovations in sustainable fabrics are further accelerating market growth across global regions.
The increasing preference for comfortable homewear has transformed sleepwear and loungewear into everyday fashion essentials. Consumers are investing in premium products made from breathable and eco-friendly materials such as organic cotton, bamboo, Tencel, and silk blends. Brands are responding by introducing fashion-forward collections that seamlessly transition from home to casual outdoor settings while offering enhanced comfort and durability.
